benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to invoice item

covered: Valid Request coverage: Multiple scenarios cover successful PUT with required and optional headers (TC01–TC05, TC21).
Non-Existing Resource coverage: 404s for non-existent/missing items (TC07, TC24, TC25).
Error handling and input validation coverage: Malformed JSON (TC08), missing header (TC09), empty body (TC10), unsupported fields (TC11), invalid invoiceItemId format (TC06), SQL injection (TC14).
Authentication/Authorization coverage: Unauthorized access scenario tested (TC13) and missing auth scenario (TC09).
Performance and scalability coverage: parallel requests across multiple items (TC20) and large payloads (TC12, TC21).
Data integrity and regression coverage: idempotency (TC17) and regression test (TC18).
Edge cases and URL variations: extra URL parameter (TC23) and state variations (TC24, TC25) and min/max field values (TC22).
gaps: Partial Update behavior not explicitly tested (whether partial field updates are rejected).
Concurrency testing directly targeting the same invoiceItemId to reveal race conditions.
403 Forbidden scenarios beyond 401 are not covered.
Rate limiting/throttling tests are not included.
Granular data-type validation for nested CustomField properties (types, ranges).
recommendations: Add a test specifically for partial update semantics to confirm API contract (reject or allow partial updates as defined).
Add concurrency stress tests targeting the same invoiceItemId to surface race conditions.
Add tests for 403 Forbidden scenarios to verify privilege checks beyond 401.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate resilience under load.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) and cache revalidation behavior.
Add more granular data-type validation tests for nested CustomField properties (types, ranges, required flags).
Expand idempotency tests with varied payloads to ensure consistent outcomes across repeated requests.
